RESISTANCE
AND
FREQUENCY
VARIATIONS
DUE
TO
UNWANTED
MODES
IN
QUARTZ
CRYSTALS
A
NUMERICAL
RELATION
IS
SHOWN
TO
EXIST
BETWEEN
THE
PEAK
RESISTANCE
INCREASE
AND
PEAK
FREQUENCY
DEPARTURE
CAUSED
BY
AN
UNWANTED
MECHANICALLY
COUPLED
MODE
THE
VALUE
PROVIDES
A
USEFUL
MEANS
OF
ESTIMATING
FREQUENCY
DEPARTURES
AND
DETERMINING
WHETHER
A
PARTICULAR
CRYSTAL
IS
SATISFACTORY
